  <Entries>
    <Entry>
      <ID>1</ID>
      <DefaultText>You withdraw the merecaster and hold it before you. 

A sour thirst immediately overtakes you, nameless and persistent. Your hands shake. Your throat is dry, dryer than sun-bleached stones.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>2</ID>
      <DefaultText>You withdraw the merecaster from your bags and the nagging, insistent thirst of the device's former owner tugs at you, scratching at your skin. </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>5</ID>
      <DefaultText>Enter the mere.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>6</ID>
      <DefaultText>Put the merecaster away. </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>7</ID>
      <DefaultText>Inspect the merecaster.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>8</ID>
      <DefaultText>Whispers rise from beneath the thirst, thoughts trapped not by the device itself, but by the maze of addiction faithfully carved within the hollows of the merecaster. 

"One drink. One taste will help me think. Why suffer? Why shouldn't I have what I want? I want this. I *deserve* this."

You lift one hand from the device, and the thoughts fade into irritable muttering. </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>9</ID>
      <DefaultText>The pull of the mere within this device slices like a polished, shining knife through the wretched cravings clutching at your throat.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>10</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
